    "term": "Summer 2026",
    "credit_hours": 3,
    "description": "Advanced programming concepts including abstract data types, details of object-oriented concepts such as encapsulation and polymorphism in a current object-oriented language as well as an introduction to object oriented analysis and design, software design patterns, and software engineering topics. The laboratory provides ample opportunity to deepen programming skills and practical experiences in current software-development technologies.",
    "prerequisites": "CPSC 17503 or equivalent",
    "learning_objectives": [
      "Research a computing problem and choose solutions from non-computing disciplines. (PI-1b)",
      "Given a set of requirements, produce a design for a software-based solution. (PI-2a)",
      "Given a set of requirements, implement a program that meets the requirements. (PI-2b)",
      "Given user requirements, develop a test plan to evaluate a computer based solution and determine its correctness. (PI-2c)",
      "Divide a complex computing problem into solvable subcomponents with appropriate data structures and algorithms. (PI-1a)"
    ]
  },
